        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 6:04PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 602 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 6 miles west of Hazelton
to 10 miles east of Linton. Another storm was located 10 miles west
of Westfield. Movement of these storms was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Linton, Strasburg, Hazelton, Hague, Westfield, Temvik, and Hull.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding in low lying areas.</instruction>
